========================================================================

1. Create Infrastructure

Create EC2-1 → Jenkins Controller (Master)
- Create Linux user (if required)
- Install Java
- Install Jenkins
- Install Jenkins Plugins
  - Git Plugin
  - Pipeline Plugin
  - Docker Pipeline Plugin
  - SonarQube Scanner Plugin
  - AWS Credentials Plugin (Only if NOT using IAM Role)
  - SSH Agent Plugin (Optional)

------------------------------------------------------------

Create EC2-2 → Jenkins Agent (Build Node)

Install:
- Java
- Git
- Docker
- Trivy
- AWS CLI
- kubectl
- Maven or Gradle (depending on the project)
- SonarScanner CLI (only if Sonar analysis runs on the agent)

Note:
Install only the tools required to execute the pipeline on the agent.
Do NOT install Jenkins or Jenkins plugins on the agent.

------------------------------------------------------------

Connect Jenkins Controller to Jenkins Agent

- Create Linux user (for example: jenkins)
- Configure SSH
- Generate SSH Key
- Copy Public Key to the Agent
- Add SSH Credentials in Jenkins
- Create Jenkins Node
- Verify the agent is online.
